The paper discusses the static analysis of a process calculus for actors, which is a programming paradigm commonly used for concurrent and distributed systems. This falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses safety properties and communication between behaviors, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the use of abstract interpretation as a framework for analysis relates to systems and control (cs.SY).
